WINDWARD ISLANDS. Mw 6.7 (GS), 6.7 (HRV). Me 6.7 (GS). Ms 6.5 (BRK). MD 5.9 (TRN). Two people injured, three houses destroyed and extensive damage in the western part of Tobago. Damage estimated at more than 25 million U.S. dollars. One of the largest known earthquakes to occur on or near Trinidad and Tobago. Seismicity in this possible triple junction zone results from the highly oblique, right- lateral collision between the Caribbean and South American plates and subduction of either the North or South American plate beneath the Caribbean plate. Note the Windward Islands magnitude 6.2 (Mw) event of April 2, located about 50 km to the north.
